Ugrad News and Updates
Latest posts from the ICS Undergraduate Student Affairs Academic Advising Blog: 




Tue, 04 Oct 2022
Add/Drop/Change Option Deadline 10/7 @5pm



The Deadline to Add/Drop/Change a Course through Webreg is Friday October 7 @ 5pm
*ICS will not approve Adds/Drops after October 7th. Exceptions after this date will only be approved for extenuating circumstances and documentation will be required. 
Course Enrollment Deadlines
Drop a course by end of week 2Add a course by end of week 2Change a grading option by the end of week 10  (After October 7th @ 5pm all grade change options will need to be submitted through an Enrollment Exception. Enrollment Exceptions can be submitted through your Student Access > Applications > Enrollment Exceptions). 
The Deadline to submit an Enrollment Exception for review is Friday December 2nd, @5pm






Thu, 04 Aug 2022
Check out our Course Updates Page!



The course updates page is where you can find a timeline of ICS course restrictions. This updated for every quarter and is subject to change. We suggest you bookmark it and check it regularly!
Check it out here.






Tue, 24 May 2022
ICS Honors Applications | Deadline: May 27, 2022



Dear ICS Students, There is still time to apply for the ICS Honors Program! As a reminder, the deadline to submit the online application is on Friday, May 27th at 5pm. Faculty References are due the following week on Friday, June 3rd at 5pm. You can find the application requirements as well as the link to the application on our Admissions Requirements and Application page.
Please note that decisions will be sent out after Spring grades have been posted. If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out. 






Tue, 10 May 2022
Writing Course Number Changes
















Tue, 03 May 2022
Research Opportunity



CEE Prof. Olivares has a great environmental contamination research opportunity for students during this summer 2022 and the next academic year, 2022-23. 
Motivated applicants are encouraged to directly email the project team leader ASAP. Please submit a one-page resume, along with an unofficial transcript to the Olivares Lab PhD student, Jialin Dong (jialind2@uci.edu) and cc Prof. Olivares (chris.olivares@uci.edu). Full application details can be found in the attached. 
